19 ha mar allo an ayr a-dhyworth an fordh syth 20 dhe'n drehedhes, meur a vydh mank 21 a-ugh ha a-woles a'n urdh bys.

query.prompt:
Please translate each line literally into English and Cornish.
70 Ne la corte del cielo, ond’ io rivegno, 71 si trovan molte gioie care e belle 72 tanto che non si posson trar del regno;
73 e ’l canto di quei lumi era di quelle; 74 chi non s’impenna sì che là sù voli, 75 dal muto aspetti quindi le novelle.

query.result:
**English:**
70 In the court of heaven, from which I return, 71 many dear and beautiful joys are found 72 so much so that they cannot be drawn from the kingdom;
73 and the song of those lights was of those joys; 74 he who does not grow wings so that he may fly up there, 75 must await the news from here in silence.
**Cornish:**
70 Y'n lys an nef, lemmyn vy'm dyworth, 71 yma moy lowena ker ha brav 72 kemmys na yllir y tynna a'n rynos;
73 ha'n kan a'n goleudhyow henna o an lowena henna; 74 neb nyns yw ow kul askel dhe hedhes bys vythkweth, 75 a wra dhe dhyskwedhes an nowodhow a-dhyworth ama.
